casebody.data:
David HOWELL v. UNIVERSAL PICTURES COMPANY, Inc. No. 9720. Circuit Court of Appeals, Ninth Circuit. March 13, 1941. H. S. Dottenheim, of Los Angeles, Cal., for appellant. Loeb & Loeb and Norman Newmark, all of Los Angeles, Cal., for appellee.

Before WILBUR, GARRECHT, and STEPHENS, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

On stipulation of counsel for respective parties ordered appeal herein dismissed, that a judgment be filed and entered accordingly, and that the mandate of this court in this cause issue forthwith.
